cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing a BCI system for human subjects to interact with a VR environment. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper involves recording brain signals using EEG devices and analyzing them to control the VR environment. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as the paper involves designing a VR headset and interface for the BCI system. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper involves analyzing facial expressions to control the VR environment. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as there is no mention of sound in the paper.
